19: Aw... It got away. You suck!
23:
What? Nooo... It's the air in this world.
It's more... friction-y.
38:
Nothing. Well, actually, something.
We're, uh, hunting, but it's nothing
you need to worry about.
49:
I just thought a good meal might
cheer everyone up, you know?
52:
Peril lies in every corner of our land,
and still you think of food and
merriment...
55:
Sorry... Maybe it was a bad idea
after all.
58:
Quite the contrary. The people
deserve to forget their troubles, if
only for a moment. I will help with
the hunt.
66: No, not at all! Thank you.
69:
My! I've never tasted anything more
delicious in my life!
73:
There's still people who haven't
eaten, child! Come here. I'll share
some of mine.
80:
Aw, I hardly did anything. Just used
those broth cubes we bought in
Palpebra.
84: To them, this may as well be a feast.
86:
Soon, it will be too dangerous for
fires. This meal was well-timed. We
owe you our gratitude
94:
I am preparing a dish of my own. It
does not sit well with me to be idle
while the young toil... And I suspect
you are still hungry.
98: I could eat a whole horse!
102:
Haha... Your hearing is as sharp as
ever, Eric.
107:
Why are you wrapping the meat in
those leaves?
110:
Smell. Can you tell how pungent
they are? When game is baked in
these leaves, it loses its stench.
113:
How intriguing... I am convinced
cooking is a form of magic.
116:
A science, perhaps, but magic? No.
Any child can learn to cook.
130:
You cut the meat, then brush on the
glaze. Then you wrap it in a leaf and
leave it by the fire.
133:
There is no magic, nor any great
feat of skill required. Come. I can see
you itching to try.
142:
...
Why are you brandishing the knife
like that?
147:
There is no need for a running start.
Stop!
153:
Sweet... yet spicy at the same time.
This is delicious!
156:
I once had to cook for a young girl,
who was one of the fussiest eaters
to walk this earth. That is when I
came up with the recipe.
158:
It's a relief nothing was spoiled... I did
not think anyone could be so
hopeless at a stove.
164:
Stella got the hang of it eventually.
In fact, I bet next time she tries, she
won't need ANY help.
171:
So why do you stand on the
battlefield?
173:
I do not call you a poor warrior. Your
companions outclass you, but that
is a testament to their
singularity—and not your mediocrity.
175:
But your eyes... I have yet to meet
one with those eyes that can
withstand the horrors of war.
177:
Are you sure this is your place, Alk?
Do you have a reason to be here?
181:
If I'm not a bad fighter... that means I
can still help, right?
184:
And yeah, I do have a reason.
Although just like the rest of me, it's
not really impressive.
188: I see... You two are birds of a feather.
194: Sharper than you look, aren't you?
198:
This Lilith's leading the Resistance,
right? What kind of person is she?
207:
Everyone calls her a "cymbal of
hope!"
212:
She has only just reached her
eighteenth year… Which would put
her around your age, Alk.
215:
I would like you to meet her and, if
possible...
218:
No, that is her decision, not mine...
Excuse me. There are still
preparations to be made.
222:
Light. Shakari taught me how to
cook.
226:
What? Is this the same Shakari
whose magic melted out the
bottom of every pot?
232:
Careful, or I may turn your wagging
tongue to ash!
